Absolute levels of global hunger in 2022 could be the highest ever, as an exceptional set of problems threaten the world. A deal to get Ukraineâ€™s trapped exports back on to the global market might help, but the war, along with the covid-19 pandemic and climate change, has exposed the fragility of the global food system. This film reveals the impact of rising food prices affecting countries worldwide, along with the civil unrest that might result, and explores the vital steps needed to lessen the impact of future food crises. 